OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F312A1780481194
OL,3,CAt least 11 people killed overnight in
OL,4,C'massive' Russian attacks on Ukraine
OL,6,FThe explosions could be heard through
OL,7,Fmost of the night and into early
OL,8,FTuesday, and recovery operations were
OL,9,Fstill underway on Tuesday morning.
OL,11,FKyiv had been bracing for another mass
OL,12,Fattack for days, after Ukrainian
OL,13,FPresident Volodymyr Zelenskyy warned
OL,14,Fthat Russia was preparing a renewed
OL,15,Fassault and urged people to remain
OL,16,Fcautious and seek shelter during air
OL,17,Fraid alerts.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G4/5
